2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Deep Neural Networks are widely used in computer vision applications, and the proposed quantization method can be applied to reduce the computational and memory costs of DNNs in computer vision tasks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Deep Neural Networks are a popular technique in artificial intelligence, and the proposed quantization method can be used to deploy complex DNNs on mobile equipment. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper deals with deep neural networks, which are a subfield of neural computing. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an optimization process for finding optimal quantization bit-width for each layer, which involves algorithmic techniques.
